  1. Use the by() function to calculate the mean pk5 score by treatment group. Are you comfortable making a conclusion about the efficacy of acupuncture based on these means? Why or why not?
by(
  data = acu$pk5, 
  INDICES = acu$group, 
  FUN = mean
)

  1. Create a scatterplot of baseline headache severity rating (horizontal axis) vs 1-year headache severity rating (vertical axis) using base R.
plot(acu$pk1, acu$pk5, xlab = "PK1", ylab = "PK5",
     main = "baseline headache severity rating vs 1-year headache severity rating")

  1. Use ggplot2to replicate (7).
acu %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = pk1, y = pk5)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  xlab("PK1") + 
  ylab("PK5") + 
  ggtitle("aseline headache severity rating vs 1-year headache severity rating")

  1. In either base R or ggplot2, take your pick, incorporate information on treatment group and sex into the plot. Consider using color, point character, point size, or other graphical elements. Be sure to include a legend.
acu %>% 
  mutate(group = factor(x = group,
                           labels = c("Group 0", "Group 1"),
                           levels = c(0, 1)),
            sex = factor(x = sex,
                         labels = c("male", "female"),
                         levels = c(0, 1))) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = pk1, y = pk5, color = group, shape = sex))  + 
  geom_point() + 
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#89ABE3FF", "#EA738DFF")) + 
  ggtitle("aseline headache severity rating vs 1-year headache severity rating")

  1. Try to replicate what you did in (9) with the other plotting platform. I.e., if you used base R, now try to replicate using ggplot (or vice versa)
cols <- c("#89ABE3FF", "#EA738DFF")
